---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>🤖 Welcome to MetaGPT!</h1>
			<p>
				Welcome to the MetaGPT blog, your comprehensive resource for understanding and implementing
				<a href="https://github.com/geekan/MetaGPT">MetaGPT</a>, the multi-agent framework that turns natural language inputs into deployable applications.
			</p>
			<p>
				MetaGPT introduces a groundbreaking approach where multiple AI agents collaborate like a software company:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>🎯 Product Manager: Clarifies requirements and sets project direction</li>
				<li>👨‍💻 Architect: Designs system architecture and technical solutions</li>
				<li>🔧 Project Manager: Breaks down tasks and manages implementation</li>
				<li>👩‍💻 Engineers: Write, review, and debug code</li>
				<li>🧪 QA Engineer: Tests and ensures code quality</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Through this blog, you'll learn:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>How to set up and configure MetaGPT for your projects</li>
				<li>Best practices for prompt engineering with multiple agents</li>
				<li>Real-world case studies and implementation examples</li>
				<li>Advanced techniques for customizing agent behaviors</li>
				<li>Tips for integrating MetaGPT with existing workflows</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Get started by exploring our <a href="/blog">blog posts</a> or learn more about the
				project in the <a href="/about">about section</a>.
			</p>
			<p>
				Join our community! Connect with other developers and share your experiences on
				<a href="https://github.com/geekan/MetaGPT/discussions">GitHub Discussions</a>.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>